Some electrical installations may have a work permit system to control access to any work being performed on or near electrical installations or equipment where potential for injury or equipment damage exists. The work permit system should set out relevant conditions for â€”
(a) accessing electrical equipment;
(b) using electrical or mechanical isolation of equipment;
(c) using safety observers;
(d) using safety equipment;
(e) restoring operational status; and
(f) other relevant matters.
NOTE Work permit systems may require practices additional to those set out in this document.
